<plot>This documentary looks at how the movie "Day of the Wolves" was made in by pioneer independent filmmaker Ferde Grofe Jr in Lake Havasu, Arizona, in 1971. Made on a shoestring budget and with the help of the McCulloch Corporation, the documentary charts the importance of the townspeople in the film's production and the early use of guerrilla filmmaking techniques.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?461716</url></doc>
